.TH IMGLOOP 1
.SH NAME
imgloop \- loop regenerating an image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgloop
[
.B -i
.I intervalms
] [
.B -c
.I cmd
...
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Display an image in a loop.  By default the image is regenerated
every 20s.  The default command is
.IR radar (1).
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/imgloop
.SH BUGS
Should allow panning.
